through sleepless nights constant physical and mental stress ?<br>
Illness, worry, stress, no time to yourself, no social life, probably little help from others ,no money, no job to help you keep your social skills and meet friends etc.<br>
<br>
You have watched a 4 year old for less than a couple of months and you say falling asleep is a choice.<br>
<br>
You have zero idea at all.<br>
<br>
This is what im trying to get at........You CAN NOT have any idea at all what it takes out of you to raise a child mentaly and physicaly until you have done it.<br>
<br>
And in this case it would have been allmost as a solo perant.<br>
<br>
If even one parent in a less than stable relationship comes here and condems this woman as you all have ill shut up.<br>
<br>
But most of us can not begin to know how hard it is to raise a child in a non nuclear family.<br>
<br>
The family &quot;unit&quot; is a wonderfull thing it provides strength support understanding help etc to all in it.<br>
<br>
Those without this but still trying to raise children need help and understanding.....not have suffering wished upon them.<br>
<br>
And falling asleep is not a choice.<br>
<br>
Ever had a rest on the couch or bed late at night while raid buffing was happening for a raid.<br>
You thought &quot;i'll just have a rest for 5 mins while they get ready then well kill X mob.<br>
Then you wake up and its 4 hours later early morning and your cold...you crawl into bed and goto sleep.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
That was not a choice to sleep<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
This can happen anytime.....a tired perant thinks &quot;i'll just have a 10 min rest now that he is in bed.<br>
<br>
2 or 3 hours later you wake up to a dead child.<br>
<br>
To condem this person is wrong.<br>
